The while loop in Java is a control flow statement that repeatedly executes a block of code as long as a given condition is true. It is an entry-controlled loop, meaning the condition is checked before the loop body is executed.
SYNTAX




while (condition) {
    // Code to be executed repeatedly
     Incerment //decerment operater
}


